title: The Amazing Race Theme - All Three Versions
description:
All three versions of The Amazing Race theme song!

The Amazing Race is an American reality competition show in which typically eleven teams of two race around the world. The race is generally split into twelve legs, with each leg requiring teams to deduce clues, navigate themselves in foreign areas, interact with locals, perform physical and mental challenges, and vie for airplane, boat, taxi, and other public transportation options on a limited budget provided by the show. Teams are progressively eliminated at the end of most legs, while the first team to arrive at the end of the final leg wins the grand prize of US$1 million. As the original version of the Amazing Race franchise, the CBS program has been running since 2001. The series concluded airing its 28th season on May 13, 2016 and has been renewed for at least one more season in 2016‚Äì17. The 29th season is scheduled to premiere mid-season during the 2016‚Äì17 television season. Numerous international versions have been developed following the same core structure, while the U.S. version is also broadcast to several other markets.

The show was created by Elise Doganieri and Bertram van Munster, who, along with Jonathan Littman, serve as executive producers. The show is produced by Earthview Inc. (headed by Doganieri and van Munster), Bruckheimer Television for CBS Television Studios and ABC Studios (a subsidiary of The Walt Disney Company). The series has been hosted by veteran New Zealand television personality Phil Keoghan since its inception.

Since the inception of the Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Reality-Competition Program in 2003, The Amazing Race has won it ten out of twelve times; the show has also won other awards and commendations. Although it has moved around several prime time slots since its inception, the program has averaged about 10 million viewers per season.

Big Brother LEAK: Spoilers for the Amazing Race 38 Crossover - Who Won?
description:
https://bit.ly/Youtube-Subscribe-BigBrother

In the next season of the Amazing Race, Big Brother alums take the spotlight. The show, will kick off on September 25th, to coincide with the season finale of Big Brother 27, creating a fascinating overlap for fans. 

The teams, made up of former Big Brother players, will jett off from LAX on March 16th, heading first for Amsterdam, the birthplace of Big Brother.

Among the participants from Big Brother were Enzo Palumbo from BB 12 and BB 22, Natalie Negroti from BB 18, Cat Dunn from BB 21, and Taylor Hale and Kyland Young from BB 24. Other notable names included Joseph Abden from BB 24, Jag Bains from BB 25, and Chelsea Bayham from BB 26.

The Amazing Race originally started (in season 1) in the Netherlands.  And will begin it's first leg there too.  The show will end with the final pit stop at Yankee Stadium, New York City, on April 9, 2025. Teams were eliminated at different points, with Enzo and his brother Jag being the first ones out. Lexi and Angela Murray from BB 26 were eliminated in Prague, Czech Republic, and the newlyweds Megan and Turner were out in Koonahora, Czech Republic.

The filming has ended and here is what we know so far from leaks. 

The remaining teams raced through Budapest, Dubrovnik, Bucharest, Athens, and finally Paris. The last three teams were Joseph and his brother Adam, Jag and his brother, and Kyland and Taylor. In the end, it was Jag Bains and his brother Jas who reportedly crossed the finish line first, securing another reality TV win for Jag.

description:

title: The Amazing Race 38 Episode 8 Recap: Bucharest Egg Chaos
description:
The Amazing Race 38 Episode Eight Recap: Egg Scramble in Bucharest

Brice Izyah and Brooke Camhi are back at the Pitstop, and this week‚Äôs Amazing Race chaos is brought to you by giant eggs, no taxis, and maximum confusion. Episode 8 of The Amazing Race Season 38 takes teams to Bucharest, Romania, where one of the funniest and most frustrating Roadblocks of the season unfolds ‚Äî and yes, those enormous painted eggs steal the entire show.

From digging through piles of oversized eggs in the park, to hauling them across town, to navigating a leg where taxis are nowhere to be found, this episode had racers scrambling in every sense. Tensions rise, alliances wobble, laughter erupts, and strategy is tested as teams push through Romania‚Äôs capital with determination (and maybe a little delusion).

Brice and Brooke break down:

title: The Amazing Race Season 38 Sneak Peek
description:
Lets GO

THE AMAZING RACE host Phil Keoghan invites some of BIG BROTHER‚Äôs fiercest former competitors to exit the house and race in the real world when 13 fan-favorite houseguests embark on a European adventure with their travel companion, on the 38th season of the CBS Original series THE AMAZING RACE, Thursday, Sept. 25 (9:00-10:30 PM, ET/PT). The Emmy¬Æ Award winner moves to its regular Wednesday time period on Wednesday, Oct. 1 (9:30-11:00 PM, ET/PT), on the CBS Television Network

The Houseguests-turned-Racers kick off the season in Amsterdam where they face classic game pieces and unexpected twists right off the bat. For the first time in THE AMAZING RACE history, teams face their first challenge before even lining up on the starting line ‚Äìthe first team to complete the task receives an express pass and the last team to complete the task faces the consequences of a Hazard. Along the route, teams will reach new heights in Prague, bathe like a king in Budapest and skydive nearly 13,000 feet over Romania.

‚ÄúTHE AMAZING RACE takes the Racers and viewers on an unforgettable journey,‚Äù said co-creators and executive producers Bertram van Munster and Elise Doganieri. ‚ÄúWith a traveling crew of over 100 people, over the course of 38 seasons, we have traveled to nearly 100 countries and over 1 million miles, an extraordinary feat of storytelling and logistics. For this season, it was fun to bring the former BIG BROTHER players out of the house and on an adventure in the real world, as the Race is a global triumph that continues to inspire and connect people all over the world.‚Äù

title: Meet Jesse & Jonathon | The Amazing Race Canada Season 11
description:
Lifelong fans of the race, these best friends are representing their 2SLGBTQIA+ community and want to look fabulous doing it. Jesse is also racing in memory of his late father, who loved watching the show, and had dreamed to one day run it with one of his kids.

Jesse Harink (he/him) 
Hometown: Sherwood Park, Alberta
Current: Vancouver, BC 
Occupation: Human Resources
Strengths: Problem solving, physical strength, and optimism/energy 
Fear/phobia: Heights
Pet peeve about your teammate: Jonathon is always right, and it‚Äôs not that he thinks he‚Äôs always right, he genuinely always is. Sometimes, when I want to outsmart Jonathon, I don‚Äôt, and it‚Äôs so frustrating.
What will you do with the prize money? There would be the responsible side, which includes RRSPs, TFSA, FHSA, and all that. After that, I would love to dedicate time to spend with my family. I moved away from Alberta more than 10 years ago and would love to come back more often to make more memories with my family, especially my nieces and nephews! Also, the goal is also to see Cher‚Äôs final tour with my mom (Cher has promised another)!

Jonathon Braun (he/him) 
Hometown: Woodlawn, Ont.
Current: Vancouver, BC
Occupation: Lawyer (Non-Profit Legal Director)
Strengths: I'm good at logic puzzles and party games. I love bringing people together and forming community. I‚Äôm also a strategist.
Fear/phobia: Enclosed spaces
Pet peeve about your teammate: Jesse emits loud belches out of nowhere. I don‚Äôt know whether I find this gross or hilarious.
What will you do with the prize money? Take my parents on a trip, and put a down payment on an apartment.

title: 'I'm single, guys!' Rubina updates relationship status after 'The Amazing Race' ouster | GOLD DERBY
description:
Rubina Bernabe and Tucker Des Lauriers met in the Big Brother 26 house, and started dating soon after the show ended. When The Amazing Race 38 came calling, Rubina ended up on a team with her sister, Kristine Bernabe, while Tucker competed alongside his brother, Eric Des Lauriers. title: IL DIVO - Amazing Grace (Live Video)
description:
Amazing Grace (Live) ‚Äì 01/06/2007
Amazing Grace (en directo)
Amazing Grace (ao vivo)


"Amazing Grace" is the closing track on Il Divo's fourth studio album, The Promise (November 2008), which peaked at No.1 on the Billboard classical chart and spent 43 straight weeks in the Top 10.
On 24 October 2008, about to leave on their post-recording vacation, Il Divo abruptly changed their travel plans to take a red-eye overseas flight to the US for a special performance of "Amazing Grace" on The Oprah Winfrey Show, after Oprah herself called to invite them.

title: Amazing Race S38 ‚Äì Episode 9 Panel Recap | GREECE BRINGS THE CHAOS!!! üî•
description:
Buckle up, Race fam‚Ä¶ because Athens, Greece gave us the MOST dramatic episode of the season‚Äîmaybe the franchise. So many ‚Äúfirsts,‚Äù so many gasps, and SO MUCH TEA spilled in this week's recap panel!

For the first time ever in Amazing Race history, we saw a LIVE Double U-Turn Vote where:
Every team got TWO votes ‚ùó

The votes determined TWO teams to be U-Turned ‚ùó

AND when the second U-Turn resulted in a TIE‚Ä¶
 ‚ûú REVOTE.
 ‚ûú STILL TIED!
 ‚ûú Result? THREE TEAMS U-TURNED!!!
 Absolute. HISTORIC. CHAOS.

And we had the perfect guests to break it all down.

üëë Reality Royalty Joins the Panel: Brendon & Rachel (Team Brenchel!)
These two are LEGENDS for a reason‚ÄîBrendon with two seasons each of BB & TAR, and Rachel with THREE of each. Their old-school perspective added so much spice, strategy, and iconic commentary (as always). Seriously‚Ä¶ we could listen to them talk strategy all day.

üî• Jas & Jag Bring the Behind-the-Scenes Tea
Our powerhouse current-season duo didn‚Äôt hold back. And can we talk about their performance?!
 They became the FIRST TEAM EVER to be U-Turned‚Ä¶ survive‚Ä¶ AND WIN THE LEG.
 An absolutely dominant showing, and the behind-the-scenes insights they shared? GOLD.

üò¢ Missing Kyland & Taylor
We were sad they couldn‚Äôt join this week, but we‚Äôre hoping to get them on a future episode‚Äîbecause you KNOW they‚Äôd have had a lot to say about this leg.

üß≠ Breaking Down the Leg Design
We dive into all the chaos surrounding the U-Turn vote and whether teams seriously misplayed their strategy.
 And then: the Detour!
"Music in the Air" versus "Olives Everywhere"

Were the tasks just too easy? Or are the remaining teams simply operating on an elite level at this point? Let us know if you agree with our panel's take!

ü™® The Sisyphean Boulder Task
The Active Route Info challenge was equal parts hilarious and brutal. Scott‚Äôs campaigning HARD to see more ARIs added to every leg‚Ä¶
 What about you? Would you have added something tougher to this leg? What challenge would YOU design if you were on production?

üëÄ Tucker & Eric‚Äôs Achilles' Heel
Fans have asked for WEEKS what these two aren‚Äôt good at‚Ä¶
 And Athens answered:
 The lowercase Greek alphabet.
 Chelsie crushed it. Tucker spiraled. And unfortunately, that spelled (literally) the end of the road for this incredibly strong team.
We hate to see Titans fall, but you could feel the shockwave and celebration at the mat from the final four teams‚Äîeverybody suddenly realizing that their chances just skyrocketed.

üé§ YOUR TURN
What were YOUR feelings about this episode?
 Did the voting strategy make sense?
 Should teams have played it differently?
 Are Jas & Jag unstoppable now??
 Tell us everything in the comments!

 üëá DROP YOUR THOUGHTS üëá
 ‚Ä¢ Who should the teams have U-Turned?
 ‚Ä¢ Were the Detour tasks too easy or perfectly balanced?
 ‚Ä¢ Do you think Jas & Jag are the team to beat now?
 We‚Äôll be replying to comments for the next 24 hours, so jump in!
 If you loved this breakdown, LIKE, SUBSCRIBE, and hit that notification bell so you don‚Äôt miss next week‚Äôs drama‚Äîwe're getting closer to the finish line and it's only getting wilder! üèÅüî•

title: Amazing Race S38 ‚Äì Episode 4 Panel Recap | Budapest Battles, Dance Triumphs & Train Trouble!
description:
This week‚Äôs episode of *The Amazing Race Season 38* had it all ‚Äî questionable travel choices, dancing victories, and one of the biggest comeback stories yet! And we‚Äôve got the perfect panel to unpack it all.

Joining us for this wild ride:
üíÉ **Hannah & Simone** ‚Äì current racers who are here to spill ALL the behind-the-scenes tea from this unforgettable leg in **Budapest, Hungary!** They open up about their controversial train decision (three stops vs. the direct sleeper train to Prague üëÄ), their *ten-attempt* Roadblock grind, and the unbelievable redemption that followed in the Detour ‚Äî a dance challenge so good Phil himself called it one of the FASTEST EVER completed on *The Amazing Race!*
üéôÔ∏è **Special Guest Fan Slot:** We‚Äôre joined by the one and only **Reality TV editor from Parade magazine** and **lead podcaster from Rob Has a Podcast (RHAP)** ‚Äî a true *Super Fan* who always brings the perfect blend of insight, humor, and tough love for all the racers.

Together, we dive deep into:
üöÇ The *train debate* that had everyone talking ‚Äî which one would YOU have chosen?
üëë The **Active Route Info: ‚ÄúSearch for a King‚Äù** ‚Äì was it too easy, or just the right amount of challenge?
üêé The **Roadblock: ‚ÄúCoach Your Carriage‚Äù** ‚Äì some teams handled it like pros, others... not so much.
üé≠ The **Detour:** ‚ÄúJuggling Act‚Äù vs. ‚ÄúBalancing Act‚Äù ‚Äì which would you have picked, and which strategy actually paid off?

This episode was packed with drama, laughter, and an inspiring story of perseverance ‚Äî and our panel doesn‚Äôt hold back in breaking it all down.

Drop a comment below:
‚û°Ô∏è What did YOU think about Hannah & Simone‚Äôs massive comeback?
‚û°Ô∏è Would you have taken the direct train or gone for the early one with stops?
‚û°Ô∏è And which Detour would have been your jam: Juggling or Balancing?

Let‚Äôs talk strategy, mishaps, and those unforgettable Budapest vibes together! üåç‚ú®

title: The Amazing Race | trailer US (2010)
description:
from the press release
Ubisoft and Ludia Inc., under a license from CBS Consumer Products, announced an all-new video game based on the smash reality television show The Amazing Race for the Nintendo Wii. Now players can participate in one of the most exciting reality games ever and compete against friends to win the ultimate challenge. The Amazing Race will be available at retailers in North America on October 26, 2010.

"Ubisoft is thrilled to be bringing The Amazing Race to fans of the game show and new players alike so that they can participate in the excitement of the show anytime they want," said Adam Novickas, U.S. director of marketing at Ubisoft.

Just like in the TV show, in The Amazing Race video game players will be tasked with using clues to overcome various challenges as they make their way through exotic locations all across the globe. The Amazing Race TV show host Phil Keoghan is featured in the game and greets players at every pit stop to read the clues, introduce challenges and give away prizes to players.

"I'm very happy that we can make everyone feel like extraordinary travelers and athletes while playing the game. I'm excited that kids and families will be able to experience the thrill of the race while competing and feel certain they will understand just how fun it is to actually compete in The Amazing Race," said Phil Keoghan, host of The Amazing Race.

The Amazing Race has been a smash reality television game show hit since 2001 and has won the Emmy Award for Outstanding Reality-Competition Program seven straight times since the category was created in 2003.

About Ubisoft
Ubisoft is a leading producer, publisher and distributor of interactive entertainment products worldwide and has grown considerably through a strong and diversified line-up of products and partnerships. Ubisoft has offices in 26 countries and has sales in more than 55 countries around the globe. It is committed to delivering high-quality, cutting-edge video game titles to consumers. For the 2009--10 fiscal year Ubisoft generated sales of 871 million euros. To learn more, please visit http://www.ubisoftgroup.com.

About Ludia Inc.
Ludia creates and distributes cross-platform interactive entertainment with mass consumer appeal. Located in Montreal and founded by experienced industry players, Ludia's innovative and high-quality product portfolio consists of original and branded properties including The Amazing Race , American Idol , The Bachelor & The Bachelorette , Family Feud , Hell's Kitchen , Hollywood Squares , Press Your Luck , The Price Is Right , Where's Waldo? and Who Wants To Be A Millionaire . To learn more please visit http://www.ludia.com.

About CBS Consumer Products
CBS Consumer Products manages worldwide licensing and merchandising for a diverse slate of television brands and series from CBS, CBS Television Studios and CBS Television Distribution, as well as from the company's extensive library of titles, and CBS Films. Additionally, the group oversees the CBS Retail Store and online sales of programming merchandise. For more information, visit http://www.cbsconsumerproducts.com.

title: Derailed in Prague:  Amazing Race 38 Ep 2 Recap
description:
üõéÔ∏è  GETRHAP.com üõéÔ∏è 

Rob Cesternino, Jessica Liese, and Mike Bloom are back for another incredible journey around the world watching The Amazing Race! Our TAR experts will be back with a recap each and every week! Make sure to also tune into our weekly exit interview with the eliminated team.

Today, Rob, Jess, and Mike discuss episode 2 of The Amazing Race 38.

The Amazing Race 38 speeds through Prague in episode 2, with Rob Cesternino, Jessica Liese, and Mike Bloom breaking down all the action. From train station chaos to towering challenges, this episode showcases the unpredictable nature of the race and the impact of sleep deprivation on team performance.

The podcast dives into the unexpected turn of events when eight teams mistakenly disembarked at the wrong Berlin stop, leading to a scramble to reach Prague. This mistake reshuffled team placements and added an extra layer of drama to the leg. The hosts discuss how exhaustion played a significant role in team decision-making, particularly for Angela and Lexi, who were ultimately eliminated.

Rob, Jessica, and Mike discuss:
- Jag and Jazz's continued dominance and strategic alliance-building
- Impact of sleep deprivation on team performance, especially for back-of-pack teams
- Megan and Matt's narrow escape from elimination for the second leg in a row
- Teams adapting to memory-based challenges, with some excelling and others struggling
- Preview of next episode's "Driver's Seat" twist, allowing one team to assign tasks to others

As teams settle into the race, alliances are forming and strategies are evolving. Will Jag and Jazz's early lead make them targets, or can they maintain their momentum? Tune in for a detailed analysis of each team's performance and insights into the race dynamics shaping this season of The Amazing Race.

title: Amazing Race 38 Week 3 Recap
description:
http://weknowamazingrace.com

Rob Cesternino, Jessica Liese, and Mike Bloom are back for another incredible journey around the world watching The Amazing Race! Our TAR experts will be back with a recap each and every week! Make sure to also tune into our weekly exit interview with the eliminated team.

Today, Jess and Mike discuss episode 3 of The Amazing Race 38.

The race wrapped up its stay in the Czech Republic with stops like Ka Hora, featuring agrarian challenges with beer, barley, straw, and hockey. The Turners were eliminated after finishing last for the third time.

The big story was the return of the Driver‚Äôs Seat, where the top three teams formed a rare alliance to assign tasks‚Äîleveraging strategy in a way rarely seen on TAR. Natalie and Stephanie gained power, directing heavier burdens to rivals while helping allies with old-school ‚ÄúMapQuest-style‚Äù directions. This raised debate about whether teamwork crossed into breaking the spirit of the race.

Team Highlights

Natalie & Stephanie: 1st, winning $2,500 and emerging as front-runners.
Jass & Jag: 2nd, intentionally holding back to avoid being targets.
Tucker & Eric: 3rd, rebounded despite major hockey struggles.
Joseph & Adam: 4th, entertaining chaos with lost keys and beer mishaps.
Hannah & Simone: 5th, adding comic relief and Czech language attempts.
Rebina & Christine: 7th, detoured early but recovered.
Kylind & Taylor: 9th, contrasting communication styles on display.
Cat & Alex: 10th, lovable chaos at the bottom.
The Turners: Eliminated after a misdirected detour and Megan‚Äôs rib injury.

What Mike and Jessica Said
They were thrilled about the return of the Driver‚Äôs Seat, calling it ‚Äúa literal tribunal‚Äù and noting it finally delivered on Phil‚Äôs promise of more strategy this season. They compared it to Survivor: Heroes vs. Villains for how alliances were used.

They joked about the ‚ÄúMapQuest‚Äù‚Äìstyle printed directions teams shared, debating whether that broke the spirit of the race and even whether trailing teams could legally grab them.

They praised Natalie & Stephanie, saying Stephanie in particular looked like a season favorite, and were impressed by Natalie scoring ‚Äúfive-hole‚Äù in the hockey Roadblock.

They laughed at Adam & Joseph‚Äôs chaos (beer pouring struggles, lost car keys) and speculated the edit was setting them up for a deep run because of all the personal backstory.

They teased Jass & Jag‚Äôs strategy, saying they ‚Äúliterally threw the comp‚Äù like Big Brother players to avoid being seen as too dominant.

They enjoyed Hannah‚Äôs comic relief and her attempts at Czech, calling it fun ‚Äúsound bite energy.‚Äù

They found Rebina & Christine‚Äôs pit stop misfire hilarious, noting it was somehow survivable thanks to how stratified the leg was.

They admitted they want Cat & Alex to stick around despite being bad racers‚Äîjust for the entertainment factor.

They were sympathetic toward the Turners‚Äô elimination, especially Megan‚Äôs rib injury, while noting the irony that it was their ‚Äúbest leg‚Äù before getting misdirected.

Looking ahead, they were excited for Budapest, praising the Rubik‚Äôs cube Fast Forward as ‚Äúbrilliant game design‚Äù because it wouldn‚Äôt just reward arriving first.

Next Stop
The race moves to Budapest, Hungary, with circus tasks, acrobatics, and a Rubik‚Äôs cube Fast Forward that won‚Äôt guarantee victory just by arriving first.

title: Strategy, Chaos & the Train Wreck Alliance! Melissa Deni Talks The Amazing Race Season 38 Ep 3
description:
SUBSCRIBE to RHAP at: https://link.chtbl.com/rhap

Host Mike Bloom welcomes Melissa Deni, fan-favorite Big Brother analyst and lifelong Amazing Race viewer, for a dive into one of the most strategic and chaotic seasons yet. This ‚Äúincredibly Big Brother-based‚Äù edition of The Amazing Race 38 has transformed the globe-trotting competition into a social strategy game‚Äîand Melissa has takes.

Melissa admits the season has ‚Äúexceeded my expectations,‚Äù praising how alliances and gameplay echo Big Brother‚Äôs best seasons. She and Mike dissect the rise of the Train Wreck Alliance‚Äîa three-team pact between Natalie Negrotti, Stephanie Negrotti, and Joseph Abdin that shared directions, gifted a birthday win, and deflected attention in true Big Brother fashion. Melissa especially loves that the alliance members‚Äîknown more for personality than cutthroat gameplay‚Äîare unexpectedly thriving strategically.

They also break down standout team performances: Jag and Jas Bains‚Äô near-perfect dominance; Natalie and Stephanie Negrotti‚Äôs surprising physical and tactical strength; and Taylor Hale and Kyland Young‚Äôs puzzling ninth-place stumble after early promise. Melissa laments the loss of Matt and Megan Turner, her favorite ‚Äúfun-quote team,‚Äù while applauding Kat Dunn and Alex Romo for their kindness and chemistry.

Along the way, Mike and Melissa unpack Amazing Race mechanics‚Äîthe Roadblock quota rule, post-leg isolation policy, and the ‚ÄúDriver‚Äôs Seat‚Äù twist that mirrors a Big Brother Head of Household power. As the Race heads to Budapest, Melissa is rooting for more personality-driven casting in future seasons‚Äîand maybe even a return for Zach Rance.

title: Peridiam Talks The Amazing Race 38
description:
Mike Bloom welcomes Peridiam for a Big Brother‚Äìflavored breakdown of The Amazing Race 38, diving into both the season and Peridiam‚Äôs personal history with the show. Peridiam explains that TAR was his ‚Äúoriginal darling‚Äù of the CBS trifecta‚Äîsomething he watched from the very beginning before drifting away and then binge-reigniting his fandom in the mid-2010s with his wife, now the bigger TAR fan. Though best known for his Big Brother and Survivor coverage, he‚Äôs touched TAR only occasionally, including a Season 5 recap once shown by Colin and Christie to their family.

From the BB perspective, Peridiam rates TAR 38 slightly above average, enjoying how knowing the alumni elevates the season. He highlights dominant frontrunners Jag & Jazz and Tucker & Eric, praises the entertainment value of teams like Izzy & Paige, and roots for pairs such as Joseph & Adam. He and Mike also unpack odd strategic decisions, early exits, and the looming double U-turn‚Äîwhere old BB tensions could finally resurface.

title: Ethanimale Talks The Amazing Race 38 Ep 9
description:
The Amazing Race 38 heads into its most dramatic stretch yet, and Mike Bloom welcomes Big Brother YouTuber, Ethanimale, on to dive into the big moves, close calls, and emotional moments shaping the final weeks. Ethanimale joins Mike to weigh in on strategy, team dynamics, and cross-show reality TV connections, highlighting the intense competition as just five teams remain.

The conversation centers on the shock elimination of Tucker and Eric, how social gameplay surfaces through tools like the U-turn vote, and the power of pre-existing relationships and Big Brother-style alliances. Ethanimale shares the emotional highs and lows from binge-watching the season, giving a fan‚Äôs perspective on how different viewing habits shape investment. Discussion also turns to the challenge design, with surprising behind-the-scenes ties to Big Brother 25 and how physicality affects female/female teams' chances.

Mike and Ethanimale discuss:
-Deep dive into the U-turn vote, exploring whether Big Brother strategy translates to The Amazing Race and how teams handle social pressure
-Ethanimale unpacks his top three emotional moments, including a non-elimination near-miss, team encouragement, and seeing friends eliminated
-Analysis of team strengths and weaknesses, such as Jag & Jas‚Äô navigation skill and Chelsea‚Äôs dynamic race with her father Jack
-Exploration of underdog success stories and how task design favors certain pairings, with Izzy and Paige‚Äôs path through tough detours in focus
-Real talk about diabetes representation in Adam‚Äôs race, with both hosts discussing the balance between pushing through and staying safe

Who holds the edge as the finale approaches‚Äîcan Joseph and Adam pull off a heroic win, or will frontrunners like Jag & Jas run away with the prize? Strategic voting, alliance secrecy, and team resilience set up a tense finish.

Catch the full episode for in-depth takes on social strategy, race mechanics, and all the behind-the-scenes details from your favorite Big Brother alumni running The Amazing Race.

description:
The Amazing Race Asia S05E01 - The Race is On!
Reupload with Better Quality

The Amazing Race Asia 5 is the fifth season of The Amazing Race Asia, a reality television game show based on the American series The Amazing Race. The fifth installment of the show returned after a 6-year hiatus and featured eleven teams of two, each with a pre-existing relationship, in a race across Southeast Asia to win US$100,000.

The season premiered on 13 October 2016 and the finale aired on 15 December 2016.

Allan Wu returned to host his fifth season of The Amazing Race Asia and eleventh season of The Amazing Race franchise overall. Wu was paired up with Tara Basro, an Indonesian film actress in hosting this season while in Indonesia.

title: The Pitstop: Amazing Race 38 Cast Assessment + Preview | Will and James
description:
Congratulations, you have checked into 'The Pit Stop', an Amazing Race Recap! After our time on #AmazingRace, it's time for us to sit back on the couch and enjoy the show again as viewers. Join us each week as we recap episodes of The Amazing Race. This is our Cast Assessment for Amazing Race Season 38 hosted by James Wallington (Season 32) & Will Jardell (Season 32).

JAMES
Instagram! http://instagram.com/whereswallington
Twitter! http://twitter.com/jameswallington

WILL
Instagram! http://instagram.com/williamjardell
Twitter! http://twitter.com/williamjardell
_____________________

Hi! We're Will and James! After meeting in 2014, we knew it was love at first sight. Our very first trip together was to New York City where we learned very quickly, that if we travel together we can do anything. Our love has continued to grow and so has our sense of adventure leading us to places all over the world. We document our travels to share with you, hoping to inspire you to grab someone you love and travel the world.  Recently, we competed on the 32nd season of The Amazing Race where we not only won the grand prize but got engaged at the finish line, the first gay/LGBT proposal in the show's 20-year history. Join us on all of our adventures!

title: The Amazing Race Season 37 Premieres March 5 with 14 Teams Competing for $1 Million
description:
Javanda Air Purifier - https://amzn.to/41WOhJ2 


The Amazing Race returns for its thrilling 37th season on March 5, 2025, at 9:30 p.m. ET on CBS. This season features a record 14 teams racing around the world for a chance at the $1 million grand prize. Contestants will face unique challenges, with a new 'Fork in the Road' twist and parallel races eliminating more teams than ever before. Hosted by Phil Keoghan, viewers can stream the episodes live on various platforms, including Paramount+, FuboTV, and DIRECTV Stream. Don't miss the season premiere titled 'Double the Stakes, Double the Eliminations'!
